263
00:12:50,847 --> 00:12:53,218
I accidentally sent it
over to Twik-Twok.

264
00:12:55,706 --> 00:12:57,066
The video we did earlier?

265
00:12:57,180 --> 00:12:59,223
- Yes.
- You sent it over?

266
00:12:59,248 --> 00:13:00,248
To Twik-Twok

267
00:13:00,789 --> 00:13:03,515
You should have had me
approve it first!

268
00:13:03,619 --> 00:13:05,559
What if we looked like idiots?

269
00:13:05,758 --> 00:13:08,378
What were you thinking?

270
00:13:08,579 --> 00:13:10,419
I’m sorry, it all happened so fast.

271
00:13:10,444 --> 00:13:13,096
I’m sorry, it won’t happen again.

272
00:13:13,121 --> 00:13:15,398
This always happens,
this isn’t the first time!

273
00:13:15,423 --> 00:13:16,655
- You don’t ever listen to me!
- I love you.

274
00:13:17,997 --> 00:13:19,344
See? Look…

275
00:13:19,369 --> 00:13:21,219
I had your face and name tattooed…
that’s you!

276
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:22,503
Why do the eyes look like that?!

277
00:13:22,825 --> 00:13:23,951
Because… oh, sorry…

278
00:13:24,084 --> 00:13:25,664
This is Randy Santiago, not you…

279
00:13:25,786 --> 00:13:27,915
- I’m sorry
- Watch yourself!

280
00:13:28,025 --> 00:13:29,365
Why did you send that!

281
00:13:29,450 --> 00:13:30,503
Because!

282
00:13:30,534 --> 00:13:32,304
- Now, it’s on me?!
- Ponpon, you sent it!

283
00:13:32,329 --> 00:13:34,318
My goodness,
now you’re blaming me, IskinePort?!

284
00:13:34,343 --> 00:13:35,451
Actually…

285
00:13:35,476 --> 00:13:36,476
Actually what?

286
00:13:36,568 --> 00:13:38,015
Pards! That’s enough!

287
00:13:40,988 --> 00:13:42,508
Stop that!

288
00:13:43,331 --> 00:13:44,924
- Stop that!
- It’s his fault!

289
00:13:44,948 --> 00:13:46,100
He messed with my phone!

290
00:13:46,202 --> 00:13:48,603
Kuya Aga, thank you!

291
00:13:49,150 --> 00:13:51,737
Ow! What is up with you two?
Why can’t you stop kissing me!

292
00:13:53,069 --> 00:13:54,102
Pose!

293
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:56,900
And post!

294
00:13:58,603 --> 00:14:01,230
Wait a minute, wait a minute!
I could hear you from outside!

295
00:14:01,443 --> 00:14:02,949
Were you fighting?

296
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:05,075
- These two!
- Would you stop!

297
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:07,681
If your Lolo Roman were alive,

298
00:14:07,747 --> 00:14:09,274
He doesn’t like any fighting!

299
00:14:09,967 --> 00:14:10,967
You know what…

300
00:14:11,499 --> 00:14:15,252
Your Lolo Roman is
very loving and tender.

301
00:14:15,687 --> 00:14:17,340
Lolo Roman is loving and tender?

302
00:14:17,365 --> 00:14:18,551
Oh, yes!

303
00:14:18,926 --> 00:14:20,546
- Well, back then…
- Lola, Lola, Lola

304
00:14:20,571 --> 00:14:22,992
- I was sulking against him
- And then?

305
00:14:23,017 --> 00:14:26,131
- And then he bought me ice cream.
- Lola, we know that story…

306
00:14:26,169 --> 00:14:27,754
You’ve told that story a million times.

307
00:14:27,779 --> 00:14:28,779
And then…

308
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:32,364
- The ice cream melted and dripped
- It dripped onto here, Lola?

309
00:14:32,389 --> 00:14:34,495
- Oh no! And then…
- And then?

310
00:14:34,565 --> 00:14:36,212
- You know he’s frugal,
- Yes?

311
00:14:36,258 --> 00:14:39,724
So he tried to…

312
00:14:44,012 --> 00:14:45,012
Ow!

313
00:14:45,165 --> 00:14:46,418
You got hit?

314
00:14:48,170 --> 00:14:50,417
OMG! Kuya, look at this, look!

315
00:14:50,442 --> 00:14:51,442
Dad?

316
00:15:04,834 --> 00:15:05,834
Eek.

317
00:15:05,859 --> 00:15:08,159
Trying to keep up with
the trend, Kuya Aga?

318
00:15:13,174 --> 00:15:15,141
O-M-G!

319
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:16,500
My love!

320
00:15:16,525 --> 00:15:18,280
Oh, this is so embarrassing!

321
00:15:18,661 --> 00:15:19,661
We have to go home!

322
00:15:19,914 --> 00:15:20,941
Tomorrow morning, first thing!

323
00:15:20,966 --> 00:15:22,169
OMG!

324
00:15:22,342 --> 00:15:23,669
I can’t believe Dad!

325
00:15:23,770 --> 00:15:29,983
I swear to God!
STG! FR, FR!

326
00:15:30,008 --> 00:15:32,634
What? What the heck is “FR, FR”?

327
00:15:32,659 --> 00:15:34,615
- For real, for real.
- For real, for real.

328
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,018
It really is for real!

329
00:15:36,043 --> 00:15:37,637
- For real… like really.
- Goodness!

330
00:15:39,566 --> 00:15:42,965
Oh wow, the comments on the
video that we made are not so nice!

331
00:15:43,210 --> 00:15:44,894
- Look!
- Oh no!

332
00:15:44,919 --> 00:15:47,071
Even Tash, Andres, and Miss Cha

333
00:15:47,682 --> 00:15:48,682
Have commented!

334
00:15:49,144 --> 00:15:50,737
They’re coming home!

335
00:15:50,848 --> 00:15:52,295
Hey! You two!

336
00:15:53,663 --> 00:15:55,222
- Who’s coming home?
- No one.

337
00:15:55,247 --> 00:15:56,495
- What do you mean coming home?
- Nothing!

338
00:15:56,542 --> 00:15:58,539
- What is that?
- It’s…

339
00:15:58,939 --> 00:16:00,525
Nothing, really!
It’s just a biscuit!

340
00:16:00,683 --> 00:16:02,356
It’s not a biscuit.
Give me your phone.

341
00:16:02,495 --> 00:16:04,675
- Iskineport has the phone.
- Give me it.

342
00:16:04,701 --> 00:16:06,668
There’s nothing on here,
why were you…

343
00:16:06,693 --> 00:16:08,535
- Give it to me, give it!
- There’s nothing here, Kuya!

344
00:16:10,072 --> 00:16:12,115
- Give me it.
- Watch it, watch it!

345
00:16:12,399 --> 00:16:13,632
Why did you tell him!

346
00:16:13,657 --> 00:16:14,657
You pointed to it!

347
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,787
- I was hiding it!
- This is what I’ve been saying.

348
00:16:18,372 --> 00:16:20,739
This is why I didn’t like
to be on social media!

349
00:16:20,764 --> 00:16:22,378
Because of these comments!

350
00:16:22,403 --> 00:16:25,418
Everyone thinks they are entitled
to a right to say mean things!

351
00:16:25,802 --> 00:16:27,162
That’s what I’ve been trying to avoid!

352
00:16:27,187 --> 00:16:29,068
That’s what I’ve been saying! Look!

353
00:16:29,229 --> 00:16:31,349
Why did you have to go there,
you were monologuing…

354
00:16:31,374 --> 00:16:33,087
- You look like an idiot!
- Give me that!

355
00:16:33,280 --> 00:16:34,940
Well we thought you
were ready for this,

356
00:16:35,003 --> 00:16:36,403
that’s why we assumed
you would be okay.

357
00:16:36,590 --> 00:16:38,296
But, Kuya Aga…

358
00:16:38,371 --> 00:16:42,078
Didn’t Ate Cha leave for Singapore
just recently to visit the two?

359
00:16:44,589 --> 00:16:47,549
She’s furious,
that’s why she’s coming home!

360
00:16:47,675 --> 00:16:49,946
- What?!
- That’s what I’ve been saying!

361
00:16:50,236 --> 00:16:52,843
We look like idiots in that video!

362
00:16:53,089 --> 00:16:55,875
That’s what I’ve been saying to you,
and to you!

363
00:16:56,335 --> 00:16:58,856
- I’m not involved in this!
- Well the more you look stupid,

364
00:16:58,881 --> 00:17:00,352
the more views you get!

365
00:17:00,377 --> 00:17:03,892
It’s true though. Look at you,
you’re always trending online

366
00:17:04,405 --> 00:17:05,405
How many views have you gotten?

367
00:17:05,810 --> 00:17:07,330
Oh, 2.5

368
00:17:07,527 --> 00:17:08,758
Why? Ow!

369
00:17:10,855 --> 00:17:11,855
Kuya,

370
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:14,728
The only reason why we did that for you
is because we want to help you.

371
00:17:14,753 --> 00:17:17,540
- Yes. Yes!
- So you get more customers.

372
00:17:18,258 --> 00:17:19,646
Hey, Iskineport!

373
00:17:20,368 --> 00:17:24,561
Will you stop? I’m telling you,
stop calling me!

374
00:17:25,099 --> 00:17:27,673
Keep in mind, I don’t like you!

375
00:17:28,252 --> 00:17:30,079
I don’t like you!

376
00:17:31,413 --> 00:17:32,420
K.O

377
00:17:33,973 --> 00:17:34,973
What is that?

378
00:17:34,998 --> 00:17:36,218
Look at it, look at it!

379
00:17:36,776 --> 00:17:38,929
It looks like bubble gum,
give me one!

380
00:17:42,830 --> 00:17:43,996
Tastes like it was imported.

381
00:17:44,296 --> 00:17:45,623
Tastes like cat dirt.

382
00:17:45,648 --> 00:17:46,649
Where did this come from?

383
00:17:46,674 --> 00:17:47,674
Oh, yeah?

384
00:17:47,864 --> 00:17:48,864
From under my shoes.

385
00:17:52,113 --> 00:17:56,226
I said look at it, not taste it!

386
00:17:57,084 --> 00:17:58,443
How are we so stupid!

387
00:17:58,530 --> 00:17:59,983
Yeah, sorry about that!

388
00:18:00,028 --> 00:18:01,028
So…

389
00:18:01,358 --> 00:18:03,258
Listen up, my tea buddies!

390
00:18:03,934 --> 00:18:08,268
He was already caught
by the spouse, but still…

391
00:18:08,458 --> 00:18:10,458
Didn’t want to admit!

392
00:18:11,081 --> 00:18:12,228
And now,

393
00:18:12,252 --> 00:18:14,658
he’s the one getting mad about it.

394
00:18:15,038 --> 00:18:16,498
Kinda thick-skinned, don’t you think?

395
00:18:16,523 --> 00:18:18,393
Mariposa, I’m done charging.
Here’s my payment.

396
00:18:18,418 --> 00:18:19,418
Ssh, quiet!

397
00:18:19,444 --> 00:18:20,784
Hello, here’s our payment.

398
00:18:21,250 --> 00:18:22,577
Sssh! Quiet!

399
00:18:22,602 --> 00:18:25,118
Ehem, ehem. I believe,

400
00:18:25,308 --> 00:18:28,902
I can ride with you until the corner,
because I left something behind.

401
00:18:28,927 --> 00:18:30,070
Why don’t you walk?

402
00:18:32,886 --> 00:18:33,980
Oh, you think that’s funny?

403
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:37,387
You want to say
that to me again?

404
00:18:38,511 --> 00:18:40,791
Next time,
don’t disrespect a lady!

405
00:18:41,854 --> 00:18:44,787
Especially not when we’ve
got a rough start to our day!

406
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,340
Couple of idiots!

407
00:18:50,234 --> 00:18:52,174
Hit him again, one more time!
He needs one more! Go ahead!

408
00:18:53,402 --> 00:18:55,106
- Oh, by the way, Boss Beauty…
- You don’t want to, huh

409
00:18:55,131 --> 00:18:56,730
How’s the sale here?

410
00:18:57,427 --> 00:18:58,427
Still slow.

411
00:18:58,708 --> 00:18:59,708
If anyone buys,

412
00:19:00,308 --> 00:19:01,308
they buy in credit.

413
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:02,827
Gosh, it’s almost the
same for everybody.

414
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:05,764
Look at Kuya Aga, it’s very early
and yet he’s on Twik-Twok!

415
00:19:06,435 --> 00:19:08,583
Actually, they owe me.

416
00:19:09,031 --> 00:19:10,331
But I can’t ask him to pay yet…

417
00:19:10,651 --> 00:19:11,711
I know they’re in lack too.

418
00:19:12,183 --> 00:19:14,777
Yeah, me too.
I feel sorry for Kuya Aga.

419
00:19:14,890 --> 00:19:16,003
Boss Beauty!

420
00:19:16,391 --> 00:19:18,278
We’ll just go on a break
to have lunch.

421
00:19:18,469 --> 00:19:19,469
Hold up, nobody leaves.

422
00:19:20,494 --> 00:19:22,781
You three, I know you’ve
been stealing from me.

423
00:19:23,572 --> 00:19:24,572
Wait, wait, wait.

424
00:19:24,667 --> 00:19:25,893
They don’t have anything with them!

425
00:19:28,157 --> 00:19:30,221
What are these then? Look!

426
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:32,840
Look! Look! Look!

427
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:34,080
They stuffed it in their belly buttons!

428
00:19:34,105 --> 00:19:35,105
Put those back!

429
00:19:35,397 --> 00:19:36,397
Put everything back!

430
00:19:37,283 --> 00:19:39,150
You thief! You took from
the expensive basket!

431
00:19:39,340 --> 00:19:40,340
What?!

432
00:19:40,946 --> 00:19:43,433
Aga has a debt amounting
to one million pesos?!

433
00:19:44,872 --> 00:19:45,872
I know!

434
00:19:46,049 --> 00:19:49,322
I didn’t really want to
throw him under the bus.

435
00:19:49,777 --> 00:19:52,427
But since you asked…

436
00:19:52,653 --> 00:19:55,240
Well, I knew that
the bakery was in debt

437
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:58,370
But a million pesos?

438
00:19:59,483 --> 00:20:03,089
Do you know who
he borrowed the money from?

439
00:20:05,430 --> 00:20:06,430
From me.

440
00:20:07,196 --> 00:20:09,849
He’s deep in debt from me.

441
00:20:10,227 --> 00:20:11,227
- Really?
- ‘Yang…

442
00:20:12,644 --> 00:20:14,537
Hey, Skineport!

443
00:20:14,562 --> 00:20:16,989
Stop that, Skineport! Right now!

444
00:20:17,014 --> 00:20:18,014
Stop it!

445
00:20:18,039 --> 00:20:21,385
I’m saying he’s deep
in debt for favors!

446
00:20:21,410 --> 00:20:22,449
- That’s what I meant!
- Oh…

447
00:20:22,660 --> 00:20:23,660
Goodness!

448
00:20:24,002 --> 00:20:25,055
I’m sorry.

449
00:20:25,108 --> 00:20:28,708
Of course, you know,
I’d do everything for Kuya Aga.

450
00:20:28,795 --> 00:20:31,815
But who does he owe money from?

451
00:20:32,305 --> 00:20:34,185
No, here’s the real situation,

452
00:20:34,452 --> 00:20:37,829
I endorsed Aga
to my business partner

453
00:20:37,854 --> 00:20:39,328
so he can loan some money.

454
00:20:39,562 --> 00:20:41,343
Oh, okay! Hey,

455
00:20:41,589 --> 00:20:45,797
Maybe, you can talk to your
Business partner slash friend.

456
00:20:45,844 --> 00:20:50,736
Maybe he can lower our debt?

457
00:20:50,932 --> 00:20:51,932
Oh, no!

458
00:20:52,049 --> 00:20:53,089
That’s complicated

459
00:20:53,804 --> 00:20:55,284
I doubt he’ll agree.

460
00:20:55,772 --> 00:20:57,099
He’s kind of a snob!

461
00:20:57,514 --> 00:20:59,107
He doesn’t like
interacting with people.

462
00:20:59,346 --> 00:21:01,640
Oh well, you know,
because he’s rich

463
00:21:02,808 --> 00:21:04,195
I’m sorry, Aga.

464
00:21:05,235 --> 00:21:08,535
I don’t face my clients.

465
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:13,116
If you can’t pay in full,

466
00:21:14,039 --> 00:21:17,319
you can pay in installment.

467
00:21:18,645 --> 00:21:19,645
Otherwise,

468
00:21:20,655 --> 00:21:23,315
I will send my men to your bakery.

469
00:21:23,613 --> 00:21:24,639
And you know

470
00:21:25,103 --> 00:21:28,282
what will happen to you and your bakery.

471
00:21:28,844 --> 00:21:31,344
I’m not threatening you, Aga!

472
00:21:31,992 --> 00:21:32,992
But know this,

473
00:21:34,158 --> 00:21:37,571
Your days are numbered.

474
00:21:45,453 --> 00:21:48,659
No one will know who I am!

475
00:21:53,154 --> 00:21:57,014
Ha! No doubt we’re right back home
in the Philippines.

476
00:21:57,481 --> 00:21:58,481
But…

477
00:21:58,528 --> 00:22:02,862
Good thing you were granted
vacation leaves from work!

478
00:22:03,131 --> 00:22:05,585
Yes, so great they gave us two weeks!

479
00:22:05,610 --> 00:22:07,620
Yes, two weeks are
more than enough!

480
00:22:07,645 --> 00:22:09,635
Thank you.

481
00:22:10,003 --> 00:22:14,836
For understanding, you know,
your Daddy… he needs our help.

482
00:22:15,153 --> 00:22:16,153
Well of course!

483
00:22:16,178 --> 00:22:18,912
You know Dad refuses everything we offer.

484
00:22:18,937 --> 00:22:20,530
A simple treat, a simple gift?

485
00:22:20,759 --> 00:22:21,759
He refuses!

486
00:22:21,784 --> 00:22:24,957
You know your dad is too proud.

487
00:22:29,844 --> 00:22:31,184
Wait, they’re here?

488
00:22:32,317 --> 00:22:33,317
Oh no!

489
00:22:33,378 --> 00:22:35,305
Kuya Aga needs to know this!

490
00:22:36,011 --> 00:22:37,271
Do I have Iskineport’s mobile number?

491
00:22:37,944 --> 00:22:38,944
Take it easy!

492
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:41,113
I’m still getting started on the sketch!

493
00:22:41,776 --> 00:22:43,956
Wow, Iskineport!

494
00:22:44,215 --> 00:22:46,535
Next time will you do my tattoo on my…

495
00:22:51,829 --> 00:22:53,083
Really, you want it there?

496
00:22:53,108 --> 00:22:54,108
Yes, I do!

497
00:22:54,133 --> 00:22:55,133
- Wanna do it now?
- Sure!

498
00:22:56,260 --> 00:22:57,907
Okay, let’s go!
Excuse me, Boss Beauty!

499
00:22:58,984 --> 00:23:01,344
I’ll do Mariposa’s tattoo now!

500
00:23:01,424 --> 00:23:02,670
You idiot, Iskineport!

501
00:23:03,401 --> 00:23:05,548
He says it’s my turn!

502
00:23:07,285 --> 00:23:09,178
My snot almost shot out!

503
00:23:10,549 --> 00:23:11,549
Hey!

504
00:23:11,668 --> 00:23:12,948
- Richard!
- Iskineport!

505
00:23:13,534 --> 00:23:16,628
I saw Ate Cha and the kids!
They’re home!

506
00:23:16,865 --> 00:23:17,865
Where?!

507
00:23:17,890 --> 00:23:18,953
You know the main road?

508
00:23:19,079 --> 00:23:20,573
Yes, the long one!

509
00:23:20,605 --> 00:23:21,605
Yes, yes, yes, that one!

510
00:23:21,737 --> 00:23:23,063
In front of the billiards place!

511
00:23:23,088 --> 00:23:25,807
Yeah, there is a billiards place
there, my classmates play there!

512
00:23:25,832 --> 00:23:28,988
Where water leaks and
there are barking dogs!

513
00:23:29,013 --> 00:23:30,659
Yeah, there are barking dogs there!

514
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,200
That’s it, that’s the place!

515
00:23:33,812 --> 00:23:35,359
Alright, Iskineport, I have to go!

516
00:23:35,384 --> 00:23:36,783
Okay, go ahead. You take care.

517
00:23:36,887 --> 00:23:37,887
Hey, Iskineport!

518
00:23:39,738 --> 00:23:40,878
What are you doing?

519
00:23:44,003 --> 00:23:46,330
I’m sketching my tattoo for you!

520
00:23:56,648 --> 00:23:57,648
Painful!

521
00:23:58,121 --> 00:23:59,383
- Excuse me!
- Oh, it’s you!

522
00:24:00,383 --> 00:24:01,383
BFF!

523
00:24:01,503 --> 00:24:03,543
You look like you’re in a rush,
where are you headed?

524
00:24:03,882 --> 00:24:05,548
Oh, nowhere important.
I just have a problem.

525
00:24:06,254 --> 00:24:08,181
Charlene came home suddenly.

526
00:24:09,098 --> 00:24:10,532
- She seems upset.
- Ooh!

527
00:24:11,402 --> 00:24:12,402
Good!

528
00:24:13,037 --> 00:24:14,037
What do you mean good?

529
00:24:15,336 --> 00:24:16,336
Food!

530
00:24:16,915 --> 00:24:17,915
I said bring them food!

531
00:24:18,379 --> 00:24:19,566
She’s just sulking,

532
00:24:19,591 --> 00:24:20,847
- Dad!
- If she’s sulk..

533
00:24:21,290 --> 00:24:22,463
Tash, hello!

534
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:24,827
Welcome back, welcome back!

535
00:24:24,852 --> 00:24:25,852
Miss you!

536
00:24:27,115 --> 00:24:28,115
Hi Karl!

537
00:24:28,635 --> 00:24:29,841
- Cha!
- My loves!

538
00:24:29,866 --> 00:24:30,866
Cha cha!

539
00:24:35,863 --> 00:24:37,530
I miss you, Karl!

540
00:24:37,610 --> 00:24:38,610
My Cha Cha.

541
00:24:38,915 --> 00:24:39,915
Cha.

542
00:24:40,143 --> 00:24:43,567
Cha Cha Cha Cha Cha Cha!

543
00:24:43,702 --> 00:24:44,702
Chef K!

544
00:24:45,386 --> 00:24:46,386
Chef K.

545
00:24:47,095 --> 00:24:48,095
Are you cold?

546
00:24:48,539 --> 00:24:49,539
Oh,

547
00:24:49,903 --> 00:24:50,903
not really!

548
00:24:51,226 --> 00:24:52,673
I’m just checking on my muscles!

549
00:24:55,405 --> 00:24:56,472
My loves!

550
00:24:59,187 --> 00:25:00,187
My loves.

551
00:25:15,722 --> 00:25:16,722
Are you on your way home?

552
00:25:17,129 --> 00:25:19,090
Okay, I’ll wait for you
by the corner!

553
00:25:38,939 --> 00:25:40,653
Orb!

554
00:25:42,034 --> 00:25:43,038
How are you?!

555
00:25:43,062 --> 00:25:44,597
Long time no see, Orb!
I’ve missed you!

556
00:25:45,192 --> 00:25:47,449
- You missed me?
- Of course, no one else but you!

557
00:25:48,038 --> 00:25:50,197
- I miss you, like so much!
- I really missed you too, Orb!

558
00:25:50,504 --> 00:25:52,664
- I’m so happy.
- I’m so happy to be back!

559
00:25:54,996 --> 00:25:56,482
I’m so happy for you
to be back.

560
00:25:56,515 --> 00:25:58,889
Me too, I’m so happy,
I can’t believe I’m seeing you!

561
00:25:59,919 --> 00:26:01,346
Oh, just… I love you!

562
00:26:02,074 --> 00:26:03,474
I’ve seen this film before.

563
00:26:03,756 --> 00:26:05,029
Kinda looks like your
father’s experience.

564
00:26:05,293 --> 00:26:07,153
He’ll start by befriending you…

565
00:26:07,178 --> 00:26:08,178
And then the next thing…

566
00:26:08,563 --> 00:26:09,630
you know what it is.

567
00:26:11,192 --> 00:26:12,192
Go back inside!

568
00:26:12,962 --> 00:26:14,102
See you later, see you later. Okay?

569
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:19,793
Dad!

570
00:26:21,725 --> 00:26:23,131
I don’t trust this guy.

571
00:26:33,143 --> 00:26:34,143
How was Singapore?

572
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:36,473
I heard it’s wonderful
out there this season.

573
00:26:36,986 --> 00:26:38,446
Such a shame
I wasn’t able to join you.

574
00:26:39,061 --> 00:26:41,381
You know debt is piling up.

575
00:26:41,762 --> 00:26:43,902
That’s why I let you do your thing.

576
00:26:44,393 --> 00:26:45,460
I respect that.

577
00:26:45,927 --> 00:26:46,927
But..

578
00:26:46,957 --> 00:26:49,110
You know we can help you, right?

579
00:26:49,405 --> 00:26:52,138
I know, but didn’t I tell you,

580
00:26:52,702 --> 00:26:55,708
if it’s a family problem,
I got it.

581
00:26:55,934 --> 00:26:57,327
There you go again!

582
00:26:57,942 --> 00:27:00,269
It’s all about your
pride for you, huh!

583
00:27:02,392 --> 00:27:03,858
- My goodness!
- My loves, hang on a second!

584
00:27:04,438 --> 00:27:05,438
My love!

585
00:27:11,945 --> 00:27:12,945
Kuya.

586
00:27:13,320 --> 00:27:15,540
How can we help Mom and Dad?

587
00:27:16,359 --> 00:27:17,359
Maybe…

588
00:27:18,012 --> 00:27:19,705
In secret?

589
00:27:19,857 --> 00:27:23,964
So he can’t refuse it?

590
00:27:24,747 --> 00:27:28,234
That sounds good!
Yeah, that’s right, we can do that!

591
00:27:28,259 --> 00:27:29,259
Kuya!

592
00:27:31,503 --> 00:27:34,003
Hey, stop! I’m up, I’m up!

593
00:27:34,342 --> 00:27:35,576
I was just playing around.

594
00:27:35,940 --> 00:27:38,530
- Relax! I have an idea.
- What idea?

595
00:27:38,555 --> 00:27:41,101
It’s simple. Look at this. Look, look!

596
00:27:42,063 --> 00:27:43,063
Yeah?

597
00:27:43,088 --> 00:27:44,513
Loan alert!

598
00:27:45,101 --> 00:27:47,648
Can’t pay? Loan is the way!

599
00:27:48,016 --> 00:27:50,583
Avoid complications, arguments away!

600
00:27:50,608 --> 00:27:53,535
- There’s your solution!
- You’re good at this, Andres!

601
00:27:53,917 --> 00:27:55,143
Make sure that’s sturdy!

602
00:27:56,658 --> 00:27:57,711
Tighten it!

603
00:27:57,736 --> 00:27:59,071
Tighten the ties!

604
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:01,924
What’s that? Ow! Ouch!
Why am I tied?

605
00:28:02,143 --> 00:28:03,676
You said to tie it tightly.

606
00:28:03,701 --> 00:28:06,458
But why are you tying me?

607
00:28:06,753 --> 00:28:07,784
Chef K,

608
00:28:07,808 --> 00:28:10,092
we’ll deposit a two-month
payment to your friend.

609
00:28:10,176 --> 00:28:12,556
But, can you please not tell Aga?

610
00:28:12,581 --> 00:28:15,351
He might get upset
with Atasha and Andres.

611
00:28:15,677 --> 00:28:17,037
Thank you, Chef K.

612
00:28:18,325 --> 00:28:20,938
Promise, I won’t tell.

613
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:24,200
Anything for you!

614
00:28:25,272 --> 00:28:27,245
I still don’t get why
you’re still with him.

615
00:28:27,307 --> 00:28:28,707
What did you just say?

616
00:28:29,380 --> 00:28:31,207
What? Nothing.

617
00:28:31,408 --> 00:28:32,595
I said…

618
00:28:32,992 --> 00:28:34,412
How did you get
to be so beautiful?

619
00:28:35,595 --> 00:28:37,309
Oh, you’re too kind, thank you.

620
00:28:37,402 --> 00:28:39,844
Oh, brother!
I have lots of stories for you!

621
00:28:40,338 --> 00:28:42,245
All of our classmates
have a crush on you!

622
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:44,433
They’re all asking
for your contact number!

623
00:28:44,486 --> 00:28:45,486
Did you give it to them?

624
00:28:45,506 --> 00:28:46,506
Of course not!

625
00:28:46,732 --> 00:28:48,705
I won’t throw you under the bus!

626
00:28:48,730 --> 00:28:51,734
And that’s why
you’re my best buddy!

627
00:28:53,815 --> 00:28:55,055
Break! Break! Break!

628
00:28:56,618 --> 00:28:57,825
Oh, so he’s like that?

629
00:28:58,580 --> 00:28:59,933
You’re so misleading!

630
00:29:02,814 --> 00:29:05,087
Hey! What is happening here?

631
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:06,859
Why is there a barricade?

632
00:29:07,235 --> 00:29:09,168
Because I heard

633
00:29:09,398 --> 00:29:10,923
that the person you
borrowed money from

634
00:29:10,968 --> 00:29:12,985
is sending his goons
over to ambush us!

635
00:29:13,089 --> 00:29:15,402
What are you fighting them off with?
You have nothing!

636
00:29:15,427 --> 00:29:17,037
And what if they have guns?

637
00:29:19,480 --> 00:29:20,480
Bullet proof.

638
00:29:21,062 --> 00:29:23,037
This is bullet proof!

639
00:29:25,761 --> 00:29:27,167
He stabbed you!

640
00:29:27,192 --> 00:29:28,854
My hair moved!

641
00:29:29,187 --> 00:29:30,187
Try it out, try it!

642
00:29:30,584 --> 00:29:31,596
Ow!

643
00:29:32,728 --> 00:29:33,995
Ouch, Kuya!

644
00:29:34,993 --> 00:29:36,229
Is it bleeding? It’s not?

645
00:29:36,813 --> 00:29:37,813
Was it just a graze?

646
00:29:38,442 --> 00:29:40,066
I thought it was bleeding!

647
00:29:40,121 --> 00:29:41,436
I’m lucky it’s just a graze!

648
00:29:42,156 --> 00:29:43,683
Oh, I wish you were hit.

649
00:29:43,725 --> 00:29:45,895
Hang on a minute!
What’s happening here?

650
00:29:46,089 --> 00:29:47,362
Iskineport.. what?

651
00:29:47,447 --> 00:29:48,968
Gosh, are you okay?

652
00:29:49,205 --> 00:29:51,154
What do you mean okay?
Can’t you see I’m bleeding? Okay?

653
00:29:51,422 --> 00:29:52,870
It’s even on my hand!

654
00:29:53,034 --> 00:29:54,068
Look at your husband!

655
00:29:54,092 --> 00:29:56,951
I said it’s bullet proof,
And he tried it out!

656
00:29:56,976 --> 00:29:58,143
He said try!

657
00:29:58,168 --> 00:29:59,907
But why on the head?!

658
00:30:00,184 --> 00:30:02,681
- I’ll wipe it off, don’t worry!
- Don’t bother!

659
00:30:02,748 --> 00:30:04,221
Your family is hurtful!

660
00:30:04,332 --> 00:30:06,762
Stop it! Don’t do that!

661
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:08,960
But it hurts!

662
00:30:08,985 --> 00:30:11,488
Long live Bake Haus of U!

663
00:30:11,543 --> 00:30:12,719
Long live!

664
00:30:12,744 --> 00:30:14,810
Long live! Long live!

665
00:30:14,835 --> 00:30:17,742
Long live Bake Haus of U!

666
00:30:17,767 --> 00:30:21,013
Long live! Long live! Long live!

667
00:30:21,054 --> 00:30:22,635
Long live Barangay Singko!

668
00:30:22,824 --> 00:30:25,963
Long live! Long live! Long live!

669
00:30:26,042 --> 00:30:27,491
Thank you, very, very much!

670
00:30:27,834 --> 00:30:29,925
I will never forget this day.

671
00:30:29,950 --> 00:30:32,893
All these help you’ve given me,
thank you. I can’t thank you enough.

672
00:30:32,918 --> 00:30:34,106
And I believe,

673
00:30:34,342 --> 00:30:39,245
That everyone here should help everyone,
especially us store owners!

674
00:30:39,270 --> 00:30:40,270
That’s right!

675
00:30:41,606 --> 00:30:43,901
So really, when the time comes,

676
00:30:43,987 --> 00:30:46,654
I will be able to pay back
all of the favors I owe.

677
00:30:46,870 --> 00:30:48,904
- That’s okay, Kuya Aga.
- Thank you!

678
00:30:48,929 --> 00:30:51,866
You can pay us back
when you’ve paid your debt.

679
00:30:53,147 --> 00:30:56,547
I believe we should all go home.

680
00:30:56,620 --> 00:30:57,687
Let’s go home.

681
00:30:57,741 --> 00:30:59,977
Why? I said it’s okay.

682
00:31:00,375 --> 00:31:01,375
Kuya! Kuya!

683
00:31:01,399 --> 00:31:02,848
- Hey! Let’s go!
- Iskineport!

684
00:31:04,111 --> 00:31:05,111
Cap, thank you, Cap!

685
00:31:05,527 --> 00:31:06,527
See!

686
00:31:06,552 --> 00:31:10,560
The kids’ solution to pay two-months
worth of debt is effective!

687
00:31:10,587 --> 00:31:12,780
No goons, no trouble!

688
00:31:12,805 --> 00:31:14,686
You idea is great, Andres!

689
00:31:14,744 --> 00:31:16,587
Thank you, my grandchildren.

690
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:20,723
Because of you…
this is a great help to your Dad.

691
00:31:20,748 --> 00:31:21,748
Of course!

692
00:31:21,773 --> 00:31:22,895
- Yeah?
- Right?

693
00:31:23,008 --> 00:31:24,014
- Um...
- Guys…

694
00:31:25,229 --> 00:31:26,229
Help?

695
00:31:31,945 --> 00:31:32,945
Help?

696
00:31:33,806 --> 00:31:35,727
- My loves…
- I asked for help?

697
00:31:36,242 --> 00:31:37,327
Let me explain.

698
00:31:37,422 --> 00:31:38,422
My loves!

699
00:31:39,116 --> 00:31:40,116
My loves!

700
00:31:47,909 --> 00:31:48,909
Sorry.

701
00:31:56,207 --> 00:31:58,195
Please place the drinks here.

702
00:32:01,497 --> 00:32:03,133
- There you go.
- Here? Oh, here.

703
00:32:03,553 --> 00:32:04,553
Is here okay?

704
00:32:05,287 --> 00:32:06,287
Okay.

705
00:32:06,536 --> 00:32:07,681
Let’s pray.

706
00:32:11,643 --> 00:32:12,643
Lord,

707
00:32:13,042 --> 00:32:17,690
thank You because Cha and
my grandchildren got home safely.

708
00:32:18,232 --> 00:32:22,475
Thank You, because there
was peace in the bakery.

709
00:32:23,405 --> 00:32:26,914
And Lord, we pray, for one of us here,

710
00:32:27,409 --> 00:32:31,076
we pray you take away his pride…

711
00:32:33,042 --> 00:32:34,042
Amen.

712
00:32:35,653 --> 00:32:36,859
And Lord,

713
00:32:38,742 --> 00:32:40,409
Thank You, because even though

714
00:32:41,173 --> 00:32:45,555
food is tight,
You still give us thy bounty.

715
00:32:46,046 --> 00:32:47,494
Thank You, Lord.

716
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:49,240
Amen.

717
00:32:52,356 --> 00:32:53,932
And Lord,

718
00:32:55,875 --> 00:33:00,403
We pray You always protect us,
and keep us.

719
00:33:00,593 --> 00:33:02,884
Thank You, very, very much.

720
00:33:03,417 --> 00:33:04,423
Amen.

721
00:33:04,448 --> 00:33:05,448
- Amen!
- Amen.

722
00:33:06,293 --> 00:33:08,456
- Let’s eat!
- Time to eat!

723
00:33:08,481 --> 00:33:11,532
You go ahead,
I’ll close up at the bakery.

724
00:33:12,205 --> 00:33:13,205
I’ll eat later.

725
00:33:13,421 --> 00:33:14,421
Ah, my love!

726
00:33:15,936 --> 00:33:17,031
- It’s okay.
- Are you sure?

727
00:33:17,862 --> 00:33:18,953
I ate yesterday.

728
00:33:22,423 --> 00:33:24,199
I’ll sit here, since Kuya
will be closing the store.

729
00:33:26,958 --> 00:33:27,958
Psst! Iski!

730
00:33:29,368 --> 00:33:30,605
- Hmm?
- Let’s go!

731
00:33:31,660 --> 00:33:32,854
We’re closing up!

732
00:33:35,115 --> 00:33:36,115
What…?

733
00:33:36,327 --> 00:33:39,152
Lola just finished
praying, we’re about to eat!

734
00:33:39,238 --> 00:33:40,238
Let’s go!

735
00:33:40,263 --> 00:33:42,027
Goodness, Lola, why did you
have to take that long to pray?

736
00:33:42,051 --> 00:33:43,784
I thought we were
attending mass!

737
00:33:44,170 --> 00:33:45,867
I forgot I ate yesterday.

738
00:33:46,545 --> 00:33:47,545
Okay, wait a second…

739
00:33:48,591 --> 00:33:50,325
I’ll just follow them to the bakery.

740
00:33:50,350 --> 00:33:52,727
I might get hungry by midnight.

741
00:33:53,127 --> 00:33:55,697
I remember I ate yesterday.

742
00:33:57,342 --> 00:33:58,342
Gosh!

743
00:33:58,544 --> 00:34:00,411
Looks like your Daddy is sulking.

744
00:34:00,848 --> 00:34:02,363
What are we gonna do?

745
00:34:04,195 --> 00:34:05,492
Water, who wants water?
You? Here you go.

746
00:34:05,535 --> 00:34:06,656
- You? Okay.
- Yes.

747
00:34:07,929 --> 00:34:09,208
What are we gonna do?

748
00:34:14,910 --> 00:34:15,910
Eat up.

749
00:34:19,187 --> 00:34:20,961
Mom, Dad left a card.

750
00:34:21,004 --> 00:34:22,004
- What?
- Look.

751
00:34:24,257 --> 00:34:26,081
I appreciate your effort.

752
00:34:26,764 --> 00:34:27,764
Thank you,

753
00:34:28,223 --> 00:34:30,259
Tash, Andres,

754
00:34:30,831 --> 00:34:32,989
and to you, my loving Cha.

755
00:34:36,083 --> 00:34:38,598
You know what, this is good.

756
00:34:39,030 --> 00:34:40,206
Baby steps.

757
00:34:40,645 --> 00:34:43,099
Your dad will slowly learn how to

758
00:34:43,322 --> 00:34:44,898
ask us for help.

759
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:48,118
Pride has no place
in the Pers family.

760
00:34:48,143 --> 00:34:49,143
Yeah.

761
00:34:49,626 --> 00:34:51,165
Okay, let’s eat! Let’s eat!

762
00:34:51,448 --> 00:34:54,703
You sit here, sit here
Atasha so you’re closer.

763
00:34:58,845 --> 00:35:00,057
See?

764
00:35:00,700 --> 00:35:04,034
That’s how our bakery started.

765
00:35:04,392 --> 00:35:07,289
Our family’s problem
is temporarily solved.

766
00:35:07,404 --> 00:35:11,222
But I promise,
our next vlog is going to be happier!

767
00:35:11,338 --> 00:35:12,338
Right, kuya?

768
00:35:14,152 --> 00:35:15,152
Ah!

769
00:35:15,177 --> 00:35:17,092
I’ll tell them who your crushes are!

770
00:35:17,117 --> 00:35:18,706
No, wait, don’t!

771
00:35:18,918 --> 00:35:20,185
But you’re sleeping!

772
00:35:20,438 --> 00:35:21,438
Wait up, wait!

773
00:35:21,826 --> 00:35:23,165
Let’s end this vlog!

774
00:35:23,353 --> 00:35:24,353
Okay, let’s do it.

775
00:35:24,773 --> 00:35:30,325
In struggles and happiness,
Pers is the first, Pers is the hero!

776
00:35:31,888 --> 00:35:33,252
Great job! Great, great job!

777
00:35:33,277 --> 00:35:35,492
Happy meet-up anniversary, my love!

778
00:35:37,673 --> 00:35:39,145
Are you forgetting something, Cha Cha?

779
00:35:39,170 --> 00:35:40,562
You were supposed to meet with me.

780
00:35:45,270 --> 00:35:46,785
Chef K, you don’t look happy.

781
00:35:46,810 --> 00:35:49,175
It’s the death anniversary
of my murdered heart.

782
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:50,718
Because of you, Aga!

783
00:35:50,904 --> 00:35:53,092
Death anniversary?

784
00:35:53,124 --> 00:35:55,671
- They helped us to make it!
- So, what is this thing that you’re up to?

785
00:35:55,754 --> 00:35:58,881
Tash and I decided
to do a food bazaar.

786
00:35:59,090 --> 00:36:00,847
You decided again
without informing me.

787
00:36:00,950 --> 00:36:05,122
The kids are just trying to
help come up with a solution

